      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"ephemeral nature\" thing sounds like a convenient excuse. I'm not talking about a server glitch or an algorithm update. I mean things are disappearing *specifically* when I try to access them. It feels targeted. Like someone is actively scrubbing my history. Do you think it's actually possible for a company to just... delete someone's trace without leaving a log?",
